───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§1 — PHYSICS INVARIANT ENFORCEMENT (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Core Principle: Single Source of Truth
ALL physics constants MUST be accessed through the physics::INVARIANTS singleton.
Direct hardcoding of these values anywhere in the codebase is a COMPLIANCE VIOLATION.
The Five Sacred Constants

Fractal Hilbert Scaling Bias (η): 5.3 (±0.05)

Accessor: physics::INVARIANTS.hilbert_scaling_bias
Formula: Replicas = ceil(log_η(Nodes))
Governs replica count calculation across the fractal lattice


Coherence Window (T₂): 1600 μs (±100 μs)

Accessor: physics::INVARIANTS.coherence_window_us
Maximum duration for synchronous operations
16× improvement over baseline transmon systems via Anderson localization


Spectral Dimension (d_s): 1.37 (±0.05)

Accessor: physics::INVARIANTS.spectral_dimension
Sierpiński gasket spectral dimension (exact: 2·log(3)/log(5))
Critical: d_s < 2 ensures all states are localized (no mobility edge)


Photonic Band Gap (PBG): 0.21 (±0.03)

Accessor: physics::INVARIANTS.photonic_band_gap
Routing overhead allowance: usable capacity = (1 - PBG) × total bandwidth
Complete TM gap in C₆ᵥ hexagonal lattice


Lock Acquisition Timeout: 100 μs (derived from T₂/16)

Accessor: physics::INVARIANTS.lock_acquisition_timeout_us
FUSE-layer atomic operation limit



Prohibited Patterns
❌ NEVER do this:
rustconst SCALING_BIAS: f64 = 5.3;  // VIOLATION
let replicas = (nodes as f64).log(5.3).ceil();  // VIOLATION
if elapsed_us > 1600 { ... }  // VIOLATION
✅ ALWAYS do this:
rustuse crate::physics::INVARIANTS;

let replicas = (nodes as f64).log(INVARIANTS.hilbert_scaling_bias).ceil();
if elapsed_us > INVARIANTS.coherence_window_us { ... }
Enforcement Mechanisms

CI Pipeline: .github/workflows/physics_audit.yml scans for magic numbers
Phase 1 Audit: AURPHYX-CURSOR-DEPLOY-002 reviews every .rs file
Runtime Validation: tests/physics/ golden-file tests verify constants
Git Hook: Commits modifying [physics] require PHYSICS OVERRIDE tag

False Positive Classification
Some numeric literals are NOT physics constants. You may use these directly:

Standard constants: 0, 1, 2, π, e, std::f64::consts::*
Array sizes: let buffer = [0u8; 1024]; (buffer capacity)
Port numbers: 8080, 3000, 6379 (network config)
Time conversions: 1000 (ms → μs), 60 (seconds → minutes)
HTTP status codes: 200, 404, 500
Bit operations: 1 << 16, 0xFF, masks and shifts
Math scaffolding: Loop bounds, indexing arithmetic unrelated to physics

When in doubt: Add a // TODO(PHYSICS_REVIEW): <explanation> comment and move on.
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§2 — TRL-4 FILE LOCKING & GOVERNANCE
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Locked Files: Public API Immutability
The [modules.validated] section in aurafs.toml defines TRL-4 LOCKED files.
These modules have been experimentally validated at Technology Readiness Level 4.
Lock Scope
PERMITTED without approval:

Internal refactoring (magic numbers → physics::INVARIANTS)
Performance optimization preserving semantics
Bug fixes that don't alter behavior contracts
Documentation improvements
Adding private helper functions

REQUIRES PHYSICS OVERRIDE governance vote (min_quorum=13):

Changing public function signatures
Adding/removing public types or traits
Modifying public struct fields
Changing module visibility (pub → pub(crate) or vice versa)
Altering physics constant usage patterns

Locked Module Categories
Core (physics + storage primitives):

src/physics/mod.rs
src/physics/invariants.rs
src/core/shard.rs
src/core/merkle.rs
src/main.rs

Network (Meshwerk topology engine):

src/network/meshwerk/mod.rs
src/network/meshwerk/roles.rs
src/network/meshwerk/routing.rs
src/network/meshwerk/topology_engine.rs
src/network/node_manager.rs
src/network/orchestrator.rs
src/network/autoheal_daemon.rs

Transports (triple-topology stack):

src/network/transport/starlink_client.rs
src/network/meshtastic_integration/firmware_bridge.rs
src/network/rns_bridge.rs
src/network/transport/udp_multicast.rs

Crypto & Audit (post-quantum primitives):

src/crypto/pqc/dilithium_sig.rs
src/audit/holographic_logger.rs
src/gov/sages.rs

AI & Compression (fractal orchestration):

src/ai/fractal_orchestrator.rs
src/compression/lattice.rs
src/compression/manager.rs

Configs:

src/network/meshwerk/configs/ghostlink.toml

Override Process
To modify a locked file's public API:

Submit governance proposal to Aurphyx LLC board
Achieve min_quorum=13 approval (Byzantine 3f+1 tolerance)
Include PHYSICS OVERRIDE tag in git commit message
CI will validate the override tag before allowing merge

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§3 — RUST CODING STANDARDS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Edition & Toolchain

Rust Edition: 2024
MSRV: 1.82.0 (Minimum Supported Rust Version)
Formatter: cargo fmt (rustfmt 2024 edition)
Linter: cargo clippy -- -D warnings (zero warnings policy)

Code Quality Standards
Naming Conventions

Types: PascalCase (e.g., PhysicsInvariants, AuraShard)
Functions/methods: snake_case (e.g., compute_replicas, fractal_replicate)
Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., MAX_SHARD_BYTES)
Modules: snake_case (e.g., physics, meshwerk)
Acronyms: Treat as words (e.g., FuseOps not FUSEOps, TrlStatus not TRLStatus)

Error Handling

Use Result<T, E> for fallible operations
Define domain-specific error types (e.g., PhysicsViolationError, CryptoError)
Avoid .unwrap() and .expect() in production code paths
Use ? operator for error propagation
Provide context with error chain libraries (e.g., anyhow, thiserror)

Documentation

All pub items require /// doc comments
Include examples in doc comments for complex functions
Link to relevant compliance documents where applicable:

rust  /// Computes optimal replica count using fractal Hilbert scaling.
  ///
  /// # Physics Basis
  ///
  /// Formula: `Replicas = ceil(log_η(Nodes))`
  /// where η = [hilbert_scaling_bias](physics::INVARIANTS::hilbert_scaling_bias)
  ///
  /// See: `compliance/ALGORITHM_PROOFS.md` Theorem 2.1
Testing

Unit tests in same file: #[cfg(test)] mod tests { ... }
Integration tests in tests/ directory
Golden-file tests for physics invariant validation
Minimum coverage thresholds (see §8)

Safety & Concurrency

Minimize unsafe usage
Any unsafe block requires:

Detailed // SAFETY: comment explaining invariants
PHYSICS OVERRIDE approval if in TRL-4 locked file


Prefer tokio for async runtime
Use Arc<RwLock<T>> or Arc<Mutex<T>> for shared state
Document lock ordering to prevent deadlocks

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§4 — CROSS-PLATFORM COMPATIBILITY
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Operating System Support

Development: Windows 11 (PowerShell)
Production: Linux (Debian/Fedora), Docker, Kubernetes
CI Targets: ubuntu-latest, windows-latest

Prohibited Patterns
❌ Platform-specific assumptions:
rustlet path = "/var/lib/aurafs";  // UNIX-only
let path = r"C:\AuraFS\data";  // Windows-only
use std::os::unix::fs::PermissionsExt;  // Without cfg guard
✅ Cross-platform abstractions:
rustuse std::path::PathBuf;
let data_dir = PathBuf::from(env::var("AURAFS_DATA_DIR").unwrap_or_else(|_| {
    if cfg!(windows) { "C:\\AuraFS\\data" } else { "/var/lib/aurafs" }
}));

#[cfg(unix)]
use std::os::unix::fs::PermissionsExt;
Banned Operations

chmod, chown without cfg(unix) guard
sudo or privilege escalation in core code
Raw / or \ path separators (use PathBuf and Path::join)
Bash scripts in critical paths (PowerShell/bash polyglot if needed)

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§5 — SECURITY & CRYPTOGRAPHY
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC)
AuraFS uses NIST-standardized quantum-resistant algorithms:
Digital Signatures: Dilithium-5 (FIPS 204 / ML-DSA-87)

Security Level: NIST Level 5
Public Key: 2,592 bytes
Signature: 4,627 bytes
Module: src/crypto/pqc/dilithium_sig.rs
Requirement: Constant-time implementation (R2 security audit)

Key Encapsulation: Kyber-1024 (FIPS 203 / ML-KEM-1024)

Security Level: NIST Level 5
Status: In-progress (R1 critical security audit)
Transitional: X25519 hybrid placeholder until Kyber integration complete
Module: src/crypto/pqc/kyber_kem.rs

Supporting Primitives

Hash: SHA3-256 (FIPS 202, quantum-resistant)
Symmetric: AES-256-GCM (FIPS 197)
Merkle Trees: SHA3-256 for shard integrity proofs

Cryptographic Best Practices

Never roll your own crypto — Use vetted libraries
Constant-time operations — Use subtle crate for comparisons
Zeroize secrets — Clear sensitive data from memory after use
Key rotation — Follow docs/key_management.md policy
Side-channel resistance — Avoid branching on secret data

Prohibited Patterns
❌ Weak or deprecated algorithms:

RSA-2048 (quantum-vulnerable)
ECDSA (quantum-vulnerable)
SHA-1 (collision-prone)
MD5 (broken)

❌ Dangerous practices:

Reusing nonces in AES-GCM
Comparing MACs with == instead of constant-time comparison
Logging or exposing private keys

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§6 — ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Shard Lifecycle State Machine
Strict three-state model enforced throughout the codebase:

Void-Shard: Raw, mutable data before lattice entry
Trap-State: Localized data packet held in coherence (NOT "cache")
Aura-Shard: Immutable, topologically protected, fractalized data

State Transition Rules
Void-Shard → Trap-State:   fractal_replicate() → localized via Anderson mechanism
Trap-State → Aura-Shard:   promote_to_aura() → immutability + topology protection
NEVER use terminology like "cache", "buffer", or "staging" for Trap-State.
This is a physics-defined coherent state, not a performance optimization.
Network Triple-Topology
Three complementary transport layers operating concurrently:

Titan-Libp2p (Primary):

High-bandwidth P2P networking
Datacenter and cloud deployment
gossipsub + Kademlia DHT


GhostLink-LoRaWAN (Secondary):

Low-power mesh for edge/IoT/off-grid
LoRa PHY + Reticulum protocol
Meshtastic firmware bridge


Starlink-HighOrbit (Tertiary):

Orbital backhaul for global coverage
Latency-tolerant bulk sync
Disaster recovery and remote sites



Meshwerk Routing
Fractal-aware routing engine respecting photonic band gap constraints:

Routing Overhead: 21% (equals photonic_band_gap)
Usable Capacity: 79% (1.0 - PBG)
Topology Engine: src/network/meshwerk/topology_engine.rs
Role-Based: Coordinator, Relay, Edge, Observer roles

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§7 — PHYSICS VIOLATION HANDLING
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Decoherence Detection
Monitor spectral dimension d_s continuously. If measurement drifts outside tolerance:
|measured_d_s - 1.37| > 0.05 → DECOHERENCE_DETECTED
Recovery Protocol

Freeze Writes: Transition to CoherenceState::DecoherenceExempt
Alert: Log to holographic_logger with CRITICAL severity
Redistribute: Trigger autoheal daemon to rebalance lattice
Validate: Confirm d_s returns to [1.32, 1.42] range
Resume: Return to CoherenceState::Strict

Implementation
rustuse crate::physics::CoherenceState;

if (measured_d_s - INVARIANTS.spectral_dimension).abs() > 0.05 {
    // Enter decoherence recovery mode
    state.set_coherence(CoherenceState::DecoherenceExempt);
    log_critical!("Spectral dimension violation: d_s={}", measured_d_s);
    autoheal_daemon.trigger_redistribution().await?;
}
Lock Timeout Enforcement
All FUSE operations acquiring locks MUST complete within lock_acquisition_timeout_us:
rustlet deadline = Instant::now() + Duration::from_micros(INVARIANTS.lock_acquisition_timeout_us);
match lock.try_acquire_until(deadline) {
    Ok(guard) => { /* perform operation */ },
    Err(_) => return Err(FuseError::LockTimeout),
}
Physics basis: 1/16 of T₂ ensures lock operations complete within coherence window.
