───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§9 — PERFORMANCE & OPTIMIZATION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Benchmarking
Use criterion.rs for performance benchmarks:
rustuse criterion::{black_box, criterion_group, criterion_main, Criterion};

fn bench_compute_replicas(c: &mut Criterion) {
    c.bench_function("compute_replicas", |b| {
        b.iter(|| compute_replicas(black_box(100)))
    });
}
Optimization Guidelines

Profile before optimizing — Use cargo flamegraph or perf
Algorithmic wins first — O(n²) → O(n log n) beats micro-optimizations
Physics constraints are immutable — You can't "optimize away" coherence limits
Zero-copy where possible — Use Cow<'a, [u8]>, &[u8] over Vec<u8> clones
Lazy evaluation — Defer expensive computations until needed

Hot Path Priorities

Shard replication — compute_replicas() called per-shard
Merkle proof verification — Happens on every read in strict mode
Lock acquisition — FUSE bottleneck, must stay under 100 μs
Gossip propagation — Network critical path, 500 ms interval

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§10 — DOCUMENTATION STANDARDS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Required Documentation
Per-Module README
Each src/*/ subfolder should contain a module-level doc comment explaining:
rust//! # Physics Module
//!
//! Core physics invariants and validation logic for AuraFS.
//!
//! ## Responsibilities
//! - Load `aurafs.toml` `[physics]` constants into `INVARIANTS` singleton
//! - Provide `PhysicsViolationError` for out-of-range detection
//! - Implement spectral dimension monitoring
//!
//! ## See Also
//! - `compliance/ALGORITHM_PROOFS.md` for mathematical foundations
//! - `compliance/PHYSICS_INVARIANTS.json` for CI validation bounds
Public API Examples
Every pub fn that's non-trivial must include a # Examples section:
rust/// Computes optimal replica count using fractal Hilbert scaling.
///
/// # Examples
///
/// ```
/// use aurafs::physics::INVARIANTS;
///
/// let replicas = compute_replicas(100);
/// assert_eq!(replicas, 3); // ceil(log_5.3(100)) ≈ 2.87 → 3
/// ```
pub fn compute_replicas(nodes: usize) -> usize {
    (nodes as f64).log(INVARIANTS.hilbert_scaling_bias).ceil() as usize
}
Compliance References
Link to authoritative documents in comments:
rust// Theorem 2.1 (compliance/ALGORITHM_PROOFS.md):
// Replicas = ceil(log_η(Nodes))
// Validated: 5.3× advantage at N=100, D=5 (VALIDATION_REPORT.md §1)
Changelog Discipline
All PRs must include a CHANGELOG.md entry under [Unreleased]:
markdown## [Unreleased]

### Added
