§12 — GIT WORKFLOW
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Branch Strategy

main: Always production-ready, protected branch
develop: Integration branch for features
feature/*: Individual features (e.g., feature/kyber-kem)
fix/*: Bug fixes
physics/*: Physics constant adjustments (requires override)

Commit Message Format
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
Types

feat: New feature
fix: Bug fix
refactor: Code restructuring without behavior change
test: Adding or updating tests
docs: Documentation changes
chore: Maintenance (dependency updates, etc.)
physics: Physics constant modification (requires PHYSICS OVERRIDE tag)

Example
feat(crypto): integrate Kyber-1024 KEM

- Implement FIPS 203 ML-KEM-1024 in src/crypto/pqc/kyber_kem.rs
- Replace X25519 hybrid placeholder
- Add round-trip encapsulate/decapsulate test
- Closes R1 from SECURITY_AUDIT.md

Refs: compliance/SECURITY_AUDIT.md R1 (CRITICAL)
