───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§13 — DEBUGGING & TROUBLESHOOTING
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Log Levels
Use structured logging via tracing crate:
rustuse tracing::{debug, info, warn, error};

debug!("Computing replicas for node_count={}", node_count);
info!("Shard promoted to Aura-Shard: shard_id={}", shard_id);
warn!("Approaching coherence window limit: elapsed={}μs", elapsed_us);
error!("Physics violation detected: d_s={}, expected=1.37±0.05", measured_d_s);
Severity Guidelines

TRACE: Hot-path micro-events (disabled in production)
DEBUG: Detailed diagnostic information
INFO: Normal operational milestones
WARN: Unusual but recoverable conditions
ERROR: Failures requiring operator attention
CRITICAL: Physics violations, Byzantine faults (holographic_logger)

Common Issues
Physics Invariant Mismatch
Symptom: CI physics_audit.yml failing
Cause: Hardcoded magic number instead of physics::INVARIANTS
Fix: Replace literal with accessor, e.g., 1600 → INVARIANTS.coherence_window_us
Lock Timeout
Symptom: FuseError::LockTimeout in production
Cause: Operation exceeding 100 μs coherence limit
Fix:

Profile the lock-holding code path
Split operation into async chunks if possible
If unavoidable, request PHYSICS OVERRIDE to extend timeout (requires justification)

Decoherence Loop
Symptom: Constant CoherenceState::DecoherenceExempt transitions
Cause: Measurement noise or actual lattice instability
Fix:

Check measurement instrumentation for sensor drift
Verify lattice geometry parameters (Hausdorff dimension, lattice constant)
Review recent network topology changes

Replica Count Explosion
Symptom: Replica count exceeding max_replicas = 1000
Cause: Incorrect node count calculation or η misconfiguration
Fix:

Validate compute_replicas() input (must be actual network node count)
Verify hilbert_scaling_bias loaded from config (not hardcoded)
Check for integer overflow in replica calculation

